                      Extending a helping hand                    There comes a time when we heed a certain call/ When the world must come together as one/ There are people dying/ Oh, and its time to lend a hand to life/ The greatest gift of all...We are the world, we are the children/ We are the ones who make a brighter day/ So lets start giving...        On May 25, the menacing cyclone, Aila, hit Sunderbans with a devastating fury, uprooting homes, belongings, farm produce and leaving cultivable fields useless for at least two years due to the inclusion of saline water that flooded the land. Many died and lakhs of people were rendered homeless, bereft and hungry. The city immediately geared up to help the victims. Eminent singers and popular bands, including Lou Majaw, Anjan Dutta, Hip Pocket, Rila Banerjee, Insomnia, Saturday Night Blues Band, Neel Adhikary, Crystal Grass, Jayshree Amyt amp; Gyan and Ishita, have joined hands to put up a two-hour rock and music concert. The concert appeals to citizens to contribute through special retail counters made available on the atrium floor for the cyclone victims. Hosted jointly by South City Mall and Trisys Communications.              Event: Save Sundarban rock concert for Aila victimsWhen: Today at 4 pm Where: Atrium, South City Mall                          
